<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="623" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">
                                <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Note by the Secretaries of the Combined Chiefs of
                                    Staff</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 341</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-09">9 September
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Review of Strategic Situation in Light of
                                    Italian Collapse</hi>
                            </p>
                            <p>The enclosure, a minute presented to the President by the Prime
                                    Minister,<note n="1" xml:id="d623fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> has been referred to the
                                Combined Staff Planners for study and for the submission of draft of
                                conclusions which may be submitted by the Combined Chiefs of Staff
                                to the President and Prime Minister on Friday afternoon, 10
                                September 1943.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Redman</hi>
                                    <lb/> J. R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Deane</hi>
                                </signed>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Combined Secretariat</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>